% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=d1c3b5 class=headings><font color=#000000>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=d1c3b5 class=headings><font color=#000000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uscarfase.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scarfase</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 9:58:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   How bout someone saying- Congratulations</span><hr size=1> I want to say Congratulations to Resolution, Fire and Fury and Awakened Souls.<br>
<br>
Simply put all of you have done great things. I read these boards on an almost daily basis and I never see anyone talk about the positive things you have done.<br>
<br>
Reso is currently owning PoM and apparently owned all of NTOV- Congratulations<br>
<br>
FnF has been owning all sorts of mobs and seem to be dominating the Warders- Congratulations<br>
<br>
AS has proven that they can take down big mobs like Vindi and Statute- Congratulations<br>
<br>
Day in and day out all I see are flames on these boards and fights amongst the guilds. I for one have friends in all three guilds and I am proud whenever the guilds do great things.  It is dissapointing that all most people see is the dark side of things.<br>
<br>
I congratulate you all and hope that you will continue to improve.<br>
<br>
<br>
Exxy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utzarothfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzaroth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 10:13:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How bout someone saying- Congratulations</span><hr size=1> They've done what tons of guilds on other servers have done. Raiding day in and day out gets you cool equipment. No huge surprise there. Why didn't you make this in Kudos? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uscarfase.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scarfase</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 10:27:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How bout someone saying- Congratulations</span><hr size=1> You know its that very same attitude that makes this forum such a drag.<br>
<br>
On other servers people are congratualted. ON FV they are flamed.<br>
<br>
It takes dedication and hard work to raid day in and day out. It takes skill to succeed. It takes patience to persevere.<br>
<br>
Why not just say Congratulations? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utzarothfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzaroth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 10:34:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How bout someone saying- Congratulations</span><hr size=1> Because, my respect is minimal for those who let this game dominate their lives in the way that hardcore raiders do. I always thought the fun of the game came in when you accomplished something like gaining a level or finishing a quest to get a new spell or breastplate. It's when the game becomes all about loot that it mirrors Diablo.<br>
<br>
I can't tell them the correct way to play the game, and by no means am I trying to. I acknowledge their abilities and what they've done on this server. However, that doesn't necessarily equate them doing something <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> for</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> this server. Make no mistakes, raiding is about self-empowerment. If it wasn't Reso, it'd be FnF, or AS. No difference to me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uscarfase.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scarfase</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 10:39:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How bout someone saying- Congratulations</span><hr size=1> So becuase others have fun in a different manner than you (that doesnt hurt you) you flame them? You have no respect for them? You can not congratulate them?<br>
<br>
I would never take up a trade skill becuase I would never spend the time doing that. Should I flame all tradecrafters? Not respect them?<br>
<br>
Why not simply acknoweldge that what people do is an accomplishment. Why not congratulate people for succeeding at what they chose to do?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarsissrazorscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarsiss Razorscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 10:40:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How bout someone saying- Congratulations</span><hr size=1> I think because on other servers those things might be accomplishments. Server firsts on FV don't mean all that much since this is the handicapped server. The mark of success here is that you are having fun. You don't really need grats for that. <p><CENTER>

