<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Go to Kudos and look. You will not find the congrats to these Guilds.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Are we required by some unwritten law to make verbal love to Reso every time they kill something? And why don't you take it upon yourself to make a thread in Kudos, instead of opening a thread in what is arguably the most popular forum? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uuininstormsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uinin Stormsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 185<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 11:40:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1193.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How bout someone saying- Congratulations</span><hr size=1> Here's part of the reason... the majority of the people on this server are not at the level where the scale of the &quot;raiding phase&quot; is evident.  At 38, I have no clue what does on in Maiden's eye, the Planes, or even Kedge Keep.<br>
<br>
Therefore, I feel no compunction to congratulate people for performing these feats because it has no bearing whatsoever on me.  <br>
<br>
I will congratulate people for bringing down Gorenaire, because that is a real and tangilble event to me.  I have rubbed Gore's (not Bloodlust) belly before, and have to kil her eventually (or Vox) for my epic.<br>
<br>
By then, of course, I will begin to have a notion of what goes into the raiding guilds, and will be more inclined to give them a hearty thumbs up.<br>
<br>
But most (not all) of the people that track that sort of thing, that really have a vested interest in that, are either already in FnF or Reso or are active open raiders that may not feel any sort of emotional attatchment to the guilds' respective accomplishments.<br>
<br>
But I could also be talking out of my ass, so take it for what its worth.<br>
<br>
Good job to all who have been successful.  Better luck next time to those who weren't.  Have fun for everyone.<br>
<br>
